01:20:58,041 --> 01:20:59,958
and make them
on the first of each month,

941
01:21:00,055 --> 01:21:02,260
as opposed to individual payoffs
to our SS contacts.

942
01:21:02,357 --> 01:21:07,535
The list is in the lower drawer
of my desk, which you--
"First of month--"

943
01:21:07,632 --> 01:21:10,413
list,
lower drawer of my desk,
which you handle...

944
01:21:10,508 --> 01:21:14,537
as cash contributions
to legitimate charities
sent to each official's office.

945
01:21:14,632 --> 01:21:17,605
Dealings with
our black market contacts,
listed as suppliers...

946
01:21:17,606 --> 01:21:21,155
in the legitimate ledger,
are more complicated.
Forget it.

947
01:21:21,250 --> 01:21:24,990
What do you mean, forget it?
You can't forget it!
It gives me a headache!

948
01:21:31,513 --> 01:21:34,772
I couldn't get you
out of here.
I'll be all right.

949
01:21:34,773 --> 01:21:38,800
Anyway, I'm here
almost every week.
Wednesdays, usually.

950
01:21:38,801 --> 01:21:42,158
I'll look in on you,
see how you're doing.

951
01:21:44,172 --> 01:21:47,719
Here, put these in your pocket.

952
01:21:47,720 --> 01:21:49,735
Come on.

953
01:21:52,419 --> 01:21:55,681
Herr Direktor,
don't let things fall apart.

954
01:21:55,776 --> 01:21:57,886
I've worked too hard.

955
01:22:05,847 --> 01:22:10,258
Thanks for-- Good luck.

956
01:22:10,354 --> 01:22:14,095
# #

957
01:22:31,166 --> 01:22:33,468
Achtung, Muetzen ab.!

958
01:22:42,962 --> 01:22:45,360
- Work!
- An die Arbeit.!

959
01:22:58,500 --> 01:22:59,938
What are you making?

960
01:23:00,226 --> 01:23:02,623
Hinges, sir.

961
01:23:05,405 --> 01:23:08,858
Ja, I've got some workers
coming in tomorrow.
Where are they from again?

962
01:23:08,953 --> 01:23:11,254
Yugoslavia, Herr Kommandant.

963
01:23:11,255 --> 01:23:13,461
I've got to make room.

964
01:23:15,763 --> 01:23:18,927
Make me a hinge. Yes, sir.

965
01:23:49,042 --> 01:23:52,112
Keep going, you're doing well.

966
01:23:52,207 --> 01:23:54,221
Says he's doing well.

967
01:24:00,647 --> 01:24:03,235
Oh, that's very good.

968
01:24:03,236 --> 01:24:07,073
But I'm a bit confused,
and perhaps you can help me.

969
01:24:07,169 --> 01:24:10,429
What I don't understand
is that you've been working...

970
01:24:10,526 --> 01:24:14,074
since I think, what,
about six this morning?

971
01:24:15,609 --> 01:24:19,828
Yet such a small pile
of hinges.

972
01:24:47,737 --> 01:24:50,517
Oh, Christ.
May I try that, sir?

973
01:24:50,518 --> 01:24:52,723
Check the angle-lever.
Maybe it's bent.

974
01:24:52,724 --> 01:24:56,081
No, no.
You wouldn't hear a click
if it was the angle-lever.

975
01:24:56,177 --> 01:24:58,479
Maybe it's the pin.
Maybe the pin shaft is greasy.
Ja, come on.

976
01:24:58,480 --> 01:25:01,452
What did I just say? Here.

977
01:25:02,795 --> 01:25:06,247
Herr Kommandant,

978
01:25:06,343 --> 01:25:10,659
I beg to report
that my heap of hinges
was so unsatisfactory...

979
01:25:10,754 --> 01:25:14,878
because the machines
were being recalibrated
this morning.

980
01:25:14,975 --> 01:25:19,674
I w-was put on
to shoveling coal.

981
01:25:42,499 --> 01:25:44,514
Strange, huh?

982
01:25:44,609 --> 01:25:46,431
Yeah.

983
01:25:51,035 --> 01:25:54,105
Thank you, Muek.

984
01:25:54,200 --> 01:25:57,940
Ah, Lisiek.
Don't touch the leather,
it's just been oiled.

985
01:25:58,037 --> 01:25:59,666
Rottenfuehrer. Oh, for me?

986
01:25:59,667 --> 01:26:03,215
Oh, thank you very much,
Herr Direktor. Thank you.
Herr Direktor!

987
01:26:03,312 --> 01:26:05,709
Herr Direktor.!

988
01:26:08,203 --> 01:26:10,696
Herr Direktor.!

989
01:26:11,847 --> 01:26:13,765
He was making hinges slowly.

990
01:26:13,860 --> 01:26:18,561
So the man can turn out a hinge
in less than a minute.
Why the long story? Hmm?

991
01:26:46,469 --> 01:26:49,155
Thank you, sir. You're welcome.

992
01:26:52,223 --> 01:26:56,059
Nobody knows
who stole the chicken, hmm?
Tell him about the chicken.

993
01:26:56,060 --> 01:27:00,664
A man walks around
with a chicken and
nobody notices this.

994
01:27:00,759 --> 01:27:03,157
Save yourselves.

995
01:27:03,253 --> 01:27:05,554
Tell him about the chicken.

996
01:27:20,612 --> 01:27:22,626
Still nobody knows.

997
01:27:33,847 --> 01:27:37,491
It was you.
You committed this crime.

998
01:27:37,492 --> 01:27:39,793
No, sir.
But you know who, though.

999
01:27:39,889 --> 01:27:42,095
Yes. Who?

1000
01:27:42,191 --> 01:27:45,068
Him!

1001
01:27:48,424 --> 01:27:52,166
He's very gifted.
Yeah, sure.
Bring him over.

1002
01:27:54,850 --> 01:27:58,591
Yes, sir. Thank you.

1003
01:28:04,441 --> 01:28:07,221
Thank you again,
Herr Direktor.
You're welcome again.

1004
01:28:07,222 --> 01:28:10,867
It's an honor to work
for such a great company.
It's great to have you.

1005
01:28:10,963 --> 01:28:14,991
I promise to learn everything
about enamelware production.
That's great.

1006
01:28:26,979 --> 01:28:31,006
Hello?
Miss Elsa Krause is here.
I only need five minutes.

1007
01:28:31,007 --> 01:28:33,692
She wants to speak
to the Herr Direktor.

1008
01:28:52,394 --> 01:28:54,505
Yes.

1009
01:28:58,532 --> 01:29:00,739
He won't see you.

1010
01:29:30,086 --> 01:29:32,100
Please, sit down.

1011
01:29:35,169 --> 01:29:37,950
Pernod? Cognac? Uh, no.

1012
01:29:39,101 --> 01:29:41,882
So, what can I do for you?

1013
01:29:45,718 --> 01:29:48,691
They say that no one dies here.

1014
01:29:48,692 --> 01:29:51,281
They say your factory
is a haven.

1015
01:29:53,967 --> 01:29:56,173
They say you are good.

1016
01:29:59,050 --> 01:30:01,159
Who says that?

1017
01:30:01,256 --> 01:30:03,269
Everyone.

1018
01:30:09,407 --> 01:30:12,189
My name is Regina Perlman,
not Elsa Krause.

1019
01:30:12,285 --> 01:30:15,354
I've been living in Krakow
on false papers since
the ghetto massacre.

1020
01:30:15,449 --> 01:30:16,889
My parents are in Plaszow.

1021
01:30:16,984 --> 01:30:21,300
Their names are
Chana and Jakob Perlman.

1022
01:30:21,396 --> 01:30:25,039
They are older people.
They are killing older people
now in Plaszow.

1023
01:30:25,040 --> 01:30:28,877
They bury them
up in the forest. Look...

1024
01:30:28,972 --> 01:30:31,754
I don't have any money.

1025
01:30:31,850 --> 01:30:34,631
I, I borrowed these clothes.

1026
01:30:37,221 --> 01:30:39,235
I'm begging you.

1027
01:30:39,330 --> 01:30:43,070
Please, please bring them here.

1028
01:30:43,167 --> 01:30:45,563
I don't do that.

1029
01:30:45,564 --> 01:30:49,400
You've been misled.
I ask one thing:

1030
01:30:49,401 --> 01:30:52,565
whether or not a worker
has certain skills.

1031
01:30:52,566 --> 01:30:55,347
My father is an importer,
not a metalworker.

1032
01:30:55,443 --> 01:30:59,183
Such activities are illegal.
You will not entrap me!

1033
01:30:59,279 --> 01:31:03,403
Cry, and I will
have you arrested.
I swear to God!

1034
01:31:12,706 --> 01:31:15,295
People die.
It's a fact of life.

1035
01:31:15,391 --> 01:31:19,036
He wants to kill everybody?
Great! What am I supposed
to do about it?

1036
01:31:19,132 --> 01:31:21,721
Bring everybody over?
Is that what you think?

1037
01:31:21,817 --> 01:31:24,597
Send them over to Schindler.
Send them all!

1038
01:31:24,598 --> 01:31:28,147
His place is a haven,
didn't you know?
It's not a factory.

1039
01:31:28,243 --> 01:31:30,447
It's not an enterprise
of any kind.

1040
01:31:30,448 --> 01:31:33,229
It's a haven for rabbis
and orphans...

1041
01:31:33,326 --> 01:31:36,490
and people with
no skills whatsoever!

1042
01:31:37,738 --> 01:31:41,861
You think I don't know
what you're doing?

1043
01:31:41,862 --> 01:31:45,314
You're so quiet
all the time.
I know, I know!

1044
01:31:45,410 --> 01:31:48,191
Are you losing money?
That's not the point!

1045
01:31:48,287 --> 01:31:52,028
What other point is--
It's dangerous!
It's dangerous to me!

1046
01:31:54,359 --> 01:31:57,811
You have to understand.
Goeth is under enormous
pressure.

1047
01:31:57,907 --> 01:32:00,976
You have to think of it
in his situation.

1048
01:32:01,072 --> 01:32:03,853
He's got this
whole place to run.

1049
01:32:03,950 --> 01:32:06,731
He's responsible
for everything here,
all these people.

1050
01:32:06,826 --> 01:32:09,703
He's got a lot of things
to worry about.

1051
01:32:09,704 --> 01:32:13,732
And he's got the war
which brings out
the worst in people.

1052
01:32:13,828 --> 01:32:17,089
Never the good,
always the bad.
Always the bad.

1053
01:32:19,294 --> 01:32:23,707
But in normal circumstances
he wouldn't be like this.
He'd be all right.

1054
01:32:23,802 --> 01:32:27,158
There'd just be the good
aspects of him which--

1055
01:32:27,159 --> 01:32:30,707
He's a wonderful crook.

1056
01:32:30,803 --> 01:32:35,023
A man who loves good food,
good wine, the ladies,
making money--

1057
01:32:35,119 --> 01:32:37,324
Killing.

1058
01:32:37,325 --> 01:32:40,010
He can't enjoy it.

1059
01:32:40,106 --> 01:32:43,079
Bejski told me the other day,
somebody escaped...

1060
01:32:43,175 --> 01:32:45,860
from a work detail
outside the wire.

1061
01:32:45,861 --> 01:32:49,697
Goeth lined up everybody
from the missing man's barracks.

1062
01:32:49,793 --> 01:32:53,724
He shot the man
to the left of Bejski,
the man to the right ofhim.

1063
01:32:53,725 --> 01:32:57,369
He walked down the line
shooting every other man
with the pistol.

1064
01:33:02,260 --> 01:33:04,659
Twenty-five.

1065
01:33:08,399 --> 01:33:11,947
What do you want me
to do about it?
Nothing, nothing.

1066
01:33:12,043 --> 01:33:14,249
We're just talking.

1067
01:33:25,470 --> 01:33:27,292
"Perlman."

1068
01:33:28,923 --> 01:33:30,936
Perlman!

1069
01:33:30,937 --> 01:33:33,621
Husband and wife.

1070
01:33:33,718 --> 01:33:37,363
Jakob and Chana Perlman!

1071
01:33:50,022 --> 01:33:53,186
Have Goldberg bring them over.

1072
01:33:55,009 --> 01:33:58,269
Muetzen ab!

1073
01:33:58,366 --> 01:34:00,380
Appell abtreten!

1074
01:34:34,715 --> 01:34:38,551
# #

1075
01:34:46,223 --> 01:34:50,155
I'm sure this will be better
than those rags, Lisiek.

1076
01:34:50,251 --> 01:34:53,992
Herr Direktor,
I was just helping Lisiek
to find something...

1077
01:34:54,087 --> 01:34:56,869
to clean the stains
from the Herr Kommandant's
bathtub.

1078
01:34:56,965 --> 01:34:59,746
Go, please.
Pardon me,
Herr Direktor.

1079
01:35:01,569 --> 01:35:06,075
You don't have to report
to me, Helen.

1080
01:35:06,076 --> 01:35:09,241
You know who I am? Hmm?

1081
01:35:16,913 --> 01:35:20,174
I'm Schindler.

1082
01:35:20,270 --> 01:35:23,243
Of course.
I-I have heard and...

1083
01:35:23,339 --> 01:35:26,217
you have been here before.

1084
01:35:28,326 --> 01:35:31,203
Here, why don't you
keep this someplace?

1085
01:35:31,300 --> 01:35:34,656
Go on, take it.
I get extra food here.

1086
01:35:34,752 --> 01:35:39,259
Well, if you don't
want to eat it, trade it.
Or give it to Lisiek.

1087
01:35:41,945 --> 01:35:44,151
Why not build yourself up?

1088
01:35:48,563 --> 01:35:52,398
My first day here,
he beat me...

1089
01:35:52,495 --> 01:35:56,235
because I threw out
the bones from dinner.

1090
01:35:59,303 --> 01:36:03,620
He came down to the basement
at midnight, and he--

1091
01:36:03,716 --> 01:36:06,305
he asked me where they were.

1092
01:36:08,703 --> 01:36:13,114
For his dogs, you understand.

1093
01:36:15,225 --> 01:36:19,157
I said to him, I--
I don't know how I say this.

1094
01:36:19,252 --> 01:36:22,610
I never could say it now--
I said to him,

1095
01:36:22,705 --> 01:36:25,007
"Why are you beating me?"

1096
01:36:28,075 --> 01:36:31,625
He said, "The reason
I beat you now..."

1097
01:36:31,720 --> 01:36:35,461
is because you ask
why I beat you."

1098
01:36:37,282 --> 01:36:40,065
I know your sufferings, Helen.

1099
01:36:42,462 --> 01:36:44,764
It doesn't matter.

1100
01:36:46,394 --> 01:36:49,271
I have accepted them.

1101
01:36:49,272 --> 01:36:51,477
Accepted them?

1102
01:36:53,204 --> 01:36:55,314
One day he will shoot me.

1103
01:36:55,409 --> 01:36:57,711
No, no, no, no,
he won't shoot you.

1104
01:36:57,807 --> 01:37:01,355
I know. I see things.

1105
01:37:01,451 --> 01:37:04,713
We were on the roof on Monday,
young Lisiek and I,

1106
01:37:04,808 --> 01:37:08,644
and we saw the Herr Kommandant
come out of the front door...

1107
01:37:08,645 --> 01:37:13,344
and down the steps by the patio
right there below us and--

1108
01:37:13,440 --> 01:37:18,139
and there on the steps
he drew his gun and he...

1109
01:37:18,235 --> 01:37:21,016
shot a woman
who was passing by.

1110
01:37:22,455 --> 01:37:25,620
A woman carrying a bundle.
Through the throat.

1111
01:37:25,716 --> 01:37:29,168
Just-- Just a woman
on her way somewhere,
you know.

1112
01:37:29,264 --> 01:37:33,005
She was no fatter or thinner...

1113
01:37:33,101 --> 01:37:35,402
or slower or faster
than anyone else,

1114
01:37:35,498 --> 01:37:39,047
and I couldn't guess
what had she done.

1115
01:37:43,650 --> 01:37:47,198
The more you see
of the Herr Kommandant,

1116
01:37:47,199 --> 01:37:51,993
the more you see
there is no set rules
that you can live by.

1117
01:37:51,994 --> 01:37:56,694
You can't say to yourself,
"If I follow these rules,
I will be safe."

1118
01:38:00,147 --> 01:38:04,269
He won't shoot you
because he enjoys you
too much.

1119
01:38:04,270 --> 01:38:08,203
He enjoys you so much
he won't even let you
wear the star.

1120
01:38:08,298 --> 01:38:10,600
He doesn't want
anyone else to know...

1121
01:38:10,696 --> 01:38:12,997
it's a Jew he's enjoying.

1122
01:38:16,259 --> 01:38:19,135
He shot the woman
from the steps...

1123
01:38:19,136 --> 01:38:22,780
because she meant
nothing to him.

1124
01:38:22,876 --> 01:38:25,177
She was one of a series,

1125
01:38:25,274 --> 01:38:27,863
neither offending
or pleasing him.

1126
01:38:31,603 --> 01:38:33,905
But you, Helen.

1127
01:38:38,221 --> 01:38:42,537
It's all right.
It's not that kind
of a kiss.

1128
01:38:46,661 --> 01:38:49,057
Thank you.

1129
01:38:49,058 --> 01:38:51,073
Shh.

1130
01:38:54,141 --> 01:38:55,964
Here.

1131
01:39:01,910 --> 01:39:04,212
Right. The wine.

1132
01:39:11,022 --> 01:39:13,898
Wonderful party, Amon.
Thank you.

1133
01:39:22,050 --> 01:39:24,832
Why do you drink
that motor oil?

1134
01:39:24,928 --> 01:39:27,900
Hmm? I send you
good stuff all the time.

1135
01:39:27,901 --> 01:39:31,738
Your liver's
going to explode
like a hand grenade.

1136
01:39:31,833 --> 01:39:34,614
The more I look at you--

1137
01:39:34,710 --> 01:39:36,916
I watch you.

1138
01:39:38,451 --> 01:39:40,464
You're never drunk.

1139
01:39:40,561 --> 01:39:44,397
Oh, that's--

1140
01:39:44,493 --> 01:39:47,465
that's real control.

1141
01:39:47,466 --> 01:39:49,576
Control is power.

1142
01:39:50,534 --> 01:39:52,741
That's power.

1143
01:39:56,385 --> 01:40:00,220
Is that why they fear us?

1144
01:40:00,221 --> 01:40:04,729
We have the fucking
power to kill, that's
why they fear us.

1145
01:40:04,824 --> 01:40:08,566
They fear us because
we have the power
to kill arbitrarily.

1146
01:40:08,661 --> 01:40:10,771
A man commits a crime,
he should know better.

1147
01:40:10,867 --> 01:40:13,360
We have him killed,
and feel good about it.

1148
01:40:13,457 --> 01:40:16,333
Or we kill him ourselves
and we feel even better.

1149
01:40:18,539 --> 01:40:21,513
That's not power, though.

1150
01:40:21,608 --> 01:40:25,637
That's justice.
It's different than power.

1151
01:40:28,226 --> 01:40:33,117
Power is when we have every
justification to kill...

1152
01:40:33,213 --> 01:40:35,707
and we don't.

1153
01:40:35,803 --> 01:40:37,912
You think that's power?

1154
01:40:40,502 --> 01:40:43,571
That's what the emperors had.
A man stole something,

1155
01:40:43,667 --> 01:40:45,202
he's brought in
before the emperor,

1156
01:40:45,297 --> 01:40:49,229
he throws himself
down on the ground,
he begs for mercy.

1157
01:40:49,326 --> 01:40:52,682
He knows he's going to die.

1158
01:40:54,504 --> 01:40:57,861
And the emperor... pardons him.

1159
01:40:59,108 --> 01:41:02,273
This worthless man.
He lets him go.

1160
01:41:05,246 --> 01:41:07,643
I think you are drunk.

1161
01:41:09,274 --> 01:41:12,151
That's power, Amon.

1162
01:41:12,247 --> 01:41:15,507
That... is power.

1163
01:41:22,893 --> 01:41:25,578
Amon the Good.

1164
01:41:28,456 --> 01:41:31,524
I pardon you.

1165
01:41:36,895 --> 01:41:39,293
What do they want?

1166
01:41:39,388 --> 01:41:42,649
I don't know,
but they're in my office now
reviewing our books.

1167
01:41:42,746 --> 01:41:45,814
As my accountant, tell me,
should I be alarmed...

1168
01:41:45,911 --> 01:41:48,692
that the auditors
are reviewing my books?
Well--

1169
01:41:48,787 --> 01:41:51,473
Or have you done
your job properly?
You needn't be alarmed.

1170
01:41:51,569 --> 01:41:53,486
I needn't be alarmed.

1171
01:41:55,980 --> 01:41:58,474
I'm sorry, sir.

1172
01:41:58,570 --> 01:42:00,583
Do you know how much
this saddle is worth?

1173
01:42:00,584 --> 01:42:03,174
Do you know how much it costs?

1174
01:42:07,681 --> 01:42:11,230
All right.

1175
01:42:11,325 --> 01:42:13,243
All right.

1176
01:42:16,505 --> 01:42:19,477
Stern, what the hell are you
doing following me around?

1177
01:42:28,301 --> 01:42:31,562
Barracken eins, elf,

