02:22:11,355 --> 02:22:15,479
Watch your step.
Men to this transport
and women to this transport.

1640
02:22:52,308 --> 02:22:56,334
Wonderful, Olek, wonderful.

1641
02:22:56,335 --> 02:23:00,556
You know how we make
ice into water?

1642
02:23:00,651 --> 02:23:03,816
Olek, get another one!

1643
02:23:40,548 --> 02:23:43,234
Alle in eine Einzelreihe
aufstellen!

1644
02:23:43,330 --> 02:23:48,413
You'll be pleased with
the level of efficiency
I get from these workers.

1645
02:23:50,043 --> 02:23:52,344
Budzyn, under my command,

1646
02:23:52,345 --> 02:23:55,414
was the envy
of every other commandant
in the labor camp system.

1647
02:23:55,509 --> 02:23:56,469
The prisoners,
however--
Excuse me.

1648
02:23:56,565 --> 02:23:59,250
They would have rather
been somewhere else.

1649
02:24:12,772 --> 02:24:16,609
The train with the women
has already left Plaszow...

1650
02:24:16,706 --> 02:24:20,062
and will be arriving
here very shortly.

1651
02:24:20,158 --> 02:24:22,746
I know you've had
a long journey.

1652
02:24:22,747 --> 02:24:25,913
But it's only a short walk
further to the factory...

1653
02:24:26,008 --> 02:24:31,186
where hot soup and bread
is waiting for you.

1654
02:24:31,283 --> 02:24:33,297
Welcome to Brinnlitz!

1655
02:24:42,504 --> 02:24:45,956
- Beans in tsunt?
- Beans are the best.

1656
02:24:45,957 --> 02:24:47,970
I don't like beans.

1657
02:24:48,067 --> 02:24:51,806
Beans and meat
and potatoes and bread.

1658
02:24:51,807 --> 02:24:53,917
That's not the way
you make tsunt.

1659
02:24:57,466 --> 02:25:00,726
Eggs in tsunt? Yes!

1660
02:25:03,316 --> 02:25:06,096
- I don't like tsunt.
- No, you don't.

1661
02:25:06,097 --> 02:25:11,084
What do you like?
I like caviar.

1662
02:25:11,180 --> 02:25:13,578
One day on the fire.

1663
02:26:16,684 --> 02:26:18,986
Alle vorm Wagen
in Position bleiben.

1664
02:26:20,424 --> 02:26:23,684
Alle in der Gruppe
zusammenbleiben.

1665
02:26:23,685 --> 02:26:27,809
Wegbleiben vom Wagen.!
Wegbleiben vom Wagen.!

1666
02:26:27,906 --> 02:26:30,207
Wegbleiben vom Wagen,
hab ich gesagt.!

1667
02:26:32,317 --> 02:26:34,619
Bagaze zostawic!

1668
02:26:36,057 --> 02:26:38,838
Schneller.!
Dalli, dalli, dalli.!

1669
02:26:38,935 --> 02:26:41,045
Was ist da hinten los.!

1670
02:26:43,538 --> 02:26:45,456
Schnell.!

1671
02:26:49,964 --> 02:26:54,087
Los, 'raus mit euch.
Zack, zack, zack! 'Raus!

1672
02:26:54,184 --> 02:26:59,746
Dreissig, fuenfunddreissig,
vierzig, fuenfundvierzig.

1673
02:26:59,842 --> 02:27:01,664
Aussteigen.!

1674
02:27:01,761 --> 02:27:04,062
'Rausgehen! 'Rausgehen!

1675
02:27:04,158 --> 02:27:06,939
Schneller! 'Rausgehen!

1676
02:27:10,104 --> 02:27:12,789
Alle 'raus!

1677
02:27:12,790 --> 02:27:16,434
Where are the listmakers?
Where are the tables?

1678
02:27:19,216 --> 02:27:21,900
Move the line.!

1679
02:27:21,997 --> 02:27:24,299
'Raus mit euch!

1680
02:27:24,394 --> 02:27:26,696
Hopp, hopp.!

1681
02:27:26,792 --> 02:27:28,806
...bagaze w wagonach.!

1682
02:27:28,902 --> 02:27:32,162
- Dalli.! 'Rausgehen.!
- Schneller.!

1683
02:27:32,163 --> 02:27:34,559
Zostawcie bagaze w wagonach.!

1684
02:27:34,560 --> 02:27:36,957
Schneller.!

1685
02:27:36,958 --> 02:27:38,781
Los, ein bisschen schneller!

1686
02:27:38,876 --> 02:27:41,657
Mama, where are we?

1687
02:27:42,329 --> 02:27:45,877
Seventeen, 18, 20--
They're in Auschwitz.

1688
02:27:45,973 --> 02:27:49,138
The train was
never routed here.
Apaperwork mistake.

1689
02:27:56,139 --> 02:27:57,674
Szybciej! Szybko!

1690
02:27:57,769 --> 02:28:00,071
Die Schuhe werfen!

1691
02:28:12,539 --> 02:28:15,320
Schneller!
Schneller!
Ubrania skladac.!

1692
02:28:17,431 --> 02:28:20,020
Pod prysznic!
Zieht euch aus!
Bewegung!

1693
02:28:20,116 --> 02:28:22,706
Bewegt euch!
Stellt euch auf
und zieht euch aus!

1694
02:28:22,801 --> 02:28:25,775
Rozbierac sie tam szybciej.!
Schneller!

1695
02:28:27,117 --> 02:28:29,899
Szybko sie rozbierac.

1696
02:28:29,994 --> 02:28:34,023
Dostaniecie mydlo
I recznik I pojdziecie
pod prysznic do dezynfeckji.!

1697
02:28:34,118 --> 02:28:36,420
Szybko sie rozbierac.!

1698
02:28:39,969 --> 02:28:42,845
Schneller!
Zabierajcie to
mydlo I szybko!

1699
02:28:42,846 --> 02:28:46,011
Zieht euch schneller aus!
Bewegung!

1700
02:28:51,094 --> 02:28:54,450
Szybko! Szybko! Sofort hinein!

1701
02:28:54,546 --> 02:28:57,136
Pojdziecie pod prysznic!
Szybko!

1702
02:28:57,232 --> 02:28:59,053
Schneller!

1703
02:28:59,150 --> 02:29:01,836
Hineim zum Bad! Schneller!

1704
02:29:03,849 --> 02:29:07,877
Schneller! Schneller!

1705
02:29:07,878 --> 02:29:10,659
Szybko! Szybko!

1706
02:29:10,754 --> 02:29:12,673
Tu wchodzic!

1707
02:31:31,737 --> 02:31:33,655
Blick hinunter.!

1708
02:31:36,341 --> 02:31:39,027
Die Hand auf die Schulter.!

1709
02:31:39,122 --> 02:31:42,000
How old are you, Mother?
Sixty-eight.

1710
02:31:42,095 --> 02:31:46,986
Cough for me, Mother.
They say to fall against
the fence is a kindness.

1711
02:31:47,083 --> 02:31:50,056
Don't kill yourself
against the fence, Clara.

1712
02:31:50,151 --> 02:31:53,891
If you do, you'll never
know what happened to you.

1713
02:31:53,988 --> 02:31:58,111
How old are you,
Mother?
Sixty-six, sir.

1714
02:31:58,112 --> 02:32:00,316
Sir? Good morning.

1715
02:32:00,317 --> 02:32:03,195
A mistake has been made.
We are not supposed
to be here.

1716
02:32:03,290 --> 02:32:06,838
We work for Oskar Schindler.
We are SchindlerJews.

1717
02:32:06,935 --> 02:32:10,291
Who is Oskar Schindler?
He had a factory
in Krakow.

1718
02:32:10,388 --> 02:32:14,606
Enamelware. A potmaker.

1719
02:32:14,607 --> 02:32:16,717
How old are you, Mother?

1720
02:32:21,130 --> 02:32:25,444
You are not
the only industrialist
who needs labor,

1721
02:32:25,541 --> 02:32:29,089
Herr Schindler.

1722
02:32:29,186 --> 02:32:31,967
I remember
earlier this year,
I.G. Farben ordered...

1723
02:32:32,062 --> 02:32:37,625
a trainload of Hungarians
for his chemical factory.

1724
02:32:37,721 --> 02:32:41,461
The train came in
through the archway,

1725
02:32:41,557 --> 02:32:46,544
and the officer in charge
of the selection went
immediately to work...

1726
02:32:46,640 --> 02:32:49,997
and sent 2,000 of them...

1727
02:32:50,092 --> 02:32:53,066
straightaway
to Special Treatment.

1728
02:32:53,162 --> 02:32:58,148
It is not my task
to interfere with the processes
that take place down here.

1729
02:32:59,875 --> 02:33:05,149
Why do you think I can
help you if I can't
help I.G. Farben?

1730
02:33:05,150 --> 02:33:07,452
Allow me to express the reason.

1731
02:33:16,467 --> 02:33:19,632
I'm not making
any judgment about you.

1732
02:33:19,728 --> 02:33:23,277
It's just that I know
that in the coming months...

1733
02:33:23,372 --> 02:33:27,401
we're all going
to need portable wealth.

1734
02:33:28,455 --> 02:33:31,045
I could have you arrested.

1735
02:33:31,141 --> 02:33:35,457
I'm protected
by powerful friends.
You should know that.

1736
02:33:38,526 --> 02:33:42,362
I do not say
I am accepting them.

1737
02:33:42,458 --> 02:33:47,061
All I say is,
I'm not comfortable
with them on the table.

1738
02:34:00,392 --> 02:34:03,558
I have a shipment
coming in tomorrow.

1739
02:34:03,653 --> 02:34:05,954
I'll cut you 300 units from it.

1740
02:34:05,955 --> 02:34:09,791
New ones. These are fresh.

1741
02:34:13,340 --> 02:34:16,599
The train comes,
we turn it around.
Mmm, yes, yes.

1742
02:34:16,600 --> 02:34:18,806
It's yours. I understand.

1743
02:34:18,902 --> 02:34:21,396
I want these.

1744
02:34:23,697 --> 02:34:26,479
You shouldn't
get stuck on names.

1745
02:34:33,960 --> 02:34:38,084
That's right. It creates
a lot of paperwork.

1746
02:34:38,563 --> 02:34:42,208
Zoldinger, Ernestina.!
Waldergrun, Hilda.!

1747
02:34:42,303 --> 02:34:44,413
Waldergrun, Leonora.!

1748
02:34:44,510 --> 02:34:47,770
Laast, Anna! Pfefferberg, Mila!

1749
02:34:47,866 --> 02:34:51,223
Dresner, Chaja! Dresner, Danka!

1750
02:34:51,318 --> 02:34:54,868
Nussbaum, Sidonia!
Rosner, Manci!

1751
02:34:54,963 --> 02:34:59,950
Hirsch, Helen.!
Grosz, Chaja Sara.!
Seelenfreund, Estella.!

1752
02:35:12,898 --> 02:35:17,022
Schneller laufen.!
Schneller laufen.! Schneller.!

1753
02:35:17,117 --> 02:35:21,049
Schneller.!
Schneller.!
Mach schon.! Voran.!

1754
02:35:23,064 --> 02:35:25,845
Los, los, los.! Schneller.!

1755
02:35:27,572 --> 02:35:31,504
- Schneller!
- Bewegt euch!

1756
02:35:31,599 --> 02:35:34,572
Bojcie sie! Bojcie sie!

1757
02:35:38,312 --> 02:35:42,437
No! No! No!

1758
02:35:46,753 --> 02:35:50,493
Maedchen, los jetzt aber!
Jetzt aber Tempo!

1759
02:35:56,247 --> 02:35:59,796
No! No! No!

1760
02:35:59,892 --> 02:36:03,249
Danka! Danka! Danka!

1761
02:36:03,344 --> 02:36:05,551
No! No! No!

1762
02:36:07,565 --> 02:36:10,921
Hey.! Hey.! Hey.!
What are you doing?

1763
02:36:11,018 --> 02:36:16,100
These are mine!
These are my workers!
They should be on my train!

1764
02:36:16,101 --> 02:36:18,689
They're skilled
munitions workers!
They're essential!

1765
02:36:18,690 --> 02:36:22,430
Essential girls!

1766
02:36:22,526 --> 02:36:27,609
Their fingers polish the insides
of shell metal casings.

1767
02:36:27,705 --> 02:36:31,445
How else am I
to polish the inside of
a .45 millimeter shell casing?

1768
02:36:31,541 --> 02:36:35,186
You tell me. You tell me!

1769
02:36:35,281 --> 02:36:39,885
Back on the train!
Back on the train!

1770
02:38:30,082 --> 02:38:34,300
Under Department "W"
provisions,

1771
02:38:34,301 --> 02:38:38,521
it is unlawful to kill
a worker without just cause.

1772
02:38:38,617 --> 02:38:41,494
Under the Businesses
Compensation Fund,

1773
02:38:41,591 --> 02:38:45,715
I am entitled to file
damage claims for such deaths.

1774
02:38:45,810 --> 02:38:48,591
If you shoot without thinking,

1775
02:38:48,688 --> 02:38:52,236
you go to prison, I get paid.

1776
02:38:52,331 --> 02:38:54,921
That's how it works.

1777
02:38:54,922 --> 02:38:59,141
So, there will be no
summary executions here.

1778
02:39:00,868 --> 02:39:05,472
There will be no
interference of any kind
with production.

1779
02:39:05,567 --> 02:39:10,362
In hopes of ensuring that,
guards will no longer be
allowed on the factory floor...

1780
02:39:10,458 --> 02:39:13,815
without my authorization.

1781
02:39:18,611 --> 02:39:22,638
For your cooperation,
you have my gratitude.

1782
02:39:23,694 --> 02:39:25,899
Come on, come.

1783
02:39:25,995 --> 02:39:28,297
Mensch, seitJahren hab' ich
so etwas nicht mehr gesehen.

1784
02:39:28,393 --> 02:39:31,942
Come on, boys, come.
Guck dir mal die Buddeln an!

1785
02:39:32,325 --> 02:39:36,736
Et dimitte nobis debita nostra,

1786
02:39:36,833 --> 02:39:40,573
sicut et nos dimittimus...

1787
02:39:40,669 --> 02:39:45,080
...quotidianum da nobis hodie,

1788
02:39:45,081 --> 02:39:49,587
et dimitte nobis
debita nostra...

1789
02:39:49,588 --> 02:39:52,945
sicut et nos dimittimus...

1790
02:39:53,040 --> 02:39:55,822
debitoribus nostris--

1791
02:39:55,918 --> 02:40:01,097
No doorman or maitre d'
will ever mistake you again.

1792
02:40:01,193 --> 02:40:03,590
I promise.

1793
02:40:03,687 --> 02:40:05,797
...sed libera nos a malo.

1794
02:40:07,427 --> 02:40:10,304
Itzhak.

1795
02:40:10,400 --> 02:40:14,045
This is Itzhak Stern,
my accountant. Itzhak--
You must be Mrs. Schindler.

1796
02:40:14,140 --> 02:40:16,537
It's a pleasure.
Emilie has volunteered
to work in the clinic.

1797
02:40:16,634 --> 02:40:18,456
Very generous of you. I know.

1798
02:40:18,552 --> 02:40:21,140
We need to talk
when you have a moment.

1799
02:40:21,141 --> 02:40:23,635
This is my wife, Stern.
I don't keep any secrets
from my spouse.

1800
02:40:23,731 --> 02:40:26,704
Oskar, please, attend
to business. It's much
more attractive.

1801
02:40:26,800 --> 02:40:28,622
Madam. Hello.

1802
02:40:28,718 --> 02:40:31,211
What is it?
We received an angry complaint
from the Armaments Board.

1803
02:40:31,308 --> 02:40:33,418
The artillery shells,
tank shells, rocket casings--

1804
02:40:33,419 --> 02:40:36,774
Apparently all of them have
failed quality control tests.
That's to be expected.

1805
02:40:36,870 --> 02:40:40,225
Start-up problems.
This isn't pots and pans.
This is a precise business.

1806
02:40:40,226 --> 02:40:41,761
I'll write them
a letter.
They're withholding payment.

1807
02:40:41,857 --> 02:40:45,884
Sure, so would I, so would you.
I wouldn't worry. We'll get it
right one of these days.

1808
02:40:45,885 --> 02:40:49,817
There's a rumor
you've been going around
miscalibrating the machines.

1809
02:40:50,489 --> 02:40:54,900
They could shut us down,
send us back to Auschwitz.

1810
02:40:55,572 --> 02:40:58,450
I'll call around, find out
where we can buy shells.

1811
02:40:58,545 --> 02:41:01,422
Pass them off as ours.
I don't see the difference
whether they're made here--

1812
02:41:01,518 --> 02:41:04,299
You don't see a difference?
I see a difference.
You lose a lot of money.

1813
02:41:04,395 --> 02:41:07,560
Fewer shells will be made.
Stern, if this factory
ever produces...

1814
02:41:07,657 --> 02:41:12,834
a shell that can
actually be fired,
I'll be very unhappy.

1815
02:41:12,835 --> 02:41:15,713
Hello, madam. How do you do?

1816
02:41:28,660 --> 02:41:32,976
How are you doing,
Rabbi? Rabbi!

1817
02:41:35,086 --> 02:41:36,908
Good, Herr Direktor.

1818
02:41:38,634 --> 02:41:41,032
Sun's going down.

1819
02:41:43,045 --> 02:41:45,539
Yes, it is.

1820
02:41:45,635 --> 02:41:49,184
What day is this?
Friday?
It is Friday, isn't it?

1821
02:41:49,279 --> 02:41:51,293
Is it?

1822
02:41:55,417 --> 02:42:00,307
What's the matter with you?
You should be preparing
for the Sabbath.

1823
02:42:00,308 --> 02:42:03,378
Shouldn't you?

1824
02:42:08,844 --> 02:42:13,447
I've got some wine.
In my office. Come.

1825
02:42:16,709 --> 02:42:20,545
Savree maranun
verbanun verabuty...

1826
02:42:22,175 --> 02:42:28,984
Baruch ata adoshem,
Elokynou melach hoyleam...

1827
02:42:28,985 --> 02:42:32,532
boyrah paree hagofan.

1828
02:42:32,533 --> 02:42:35,410
Amen.

1829
02:42:35,411 --> 02:42:38,576
Baruch ata adoshem elokynou
melach hoyleam.

1830
02:42:38,671 --> 02:42:41,549
Asher kideshanou
bamezvoytaiv veratzah banou...

1831
02:42:41,644 --> 02:42:47,111
ve shabath kodshoy beahava ve
razoun hencheelanou...

1832
02:42:47,207 --> 02:42:50,275
zicarone lemahsa barashit...

1833
02:42:50,372 --> 02:42:55,168
yhom techelah lemikrahy kodesh
zecher letzeat Mitzraim.

1834
02:42:55,263 --> 02:43:01,593
Kee banou bachartah veotanou
kedashtah mekol ahameem.

1835
02:43:01,689 --> 02:43:06,772
Ve Shabath kodshou beahava
ve razoun hencheltanou...

1836
02:43:06,868 --> 02:43:12,814
Barooch ata adoshem
mekadesh hashabat.

1837
02:43:12,910 --> 02:43:14,732
Geet Shabath.

1838
02:43:14,828 --> 02:43:16,938
Geet Shabath.

1839
02:43:25,378 --> 02:43:28,350
What?

1840
02:43:28,351 --> 02:43:33,146
Do you have any money,
uh, hidden away someplace...

1841
02:43:33,147 --> 02:43:35,831
that I don't know about?

1842
02:43:39,093 --> 02:43:41,490
No.

1843
02:43:45,710 --> 02:43:49,451
Why? Am I broke?

1844
02:43:49,546 --> 02:43:52,327
Uh--

1845
02:43:52,423 --> 02:43:55,205
Well--

1846
02:43:55,301 --> 02:44:00,768
Yesterday morning, at 241 a.m.,

1847
02:44:00,863 --> 02:44:05,275
at General Eisenhower's
headquarters,

1848
02:44:05,371 --> 02:44:07,960
General Jodl...

1849
02:44:08,056 --> 02:44:11,507
signed the "Act of
Unconditional Surrender"...

1850
02:44:11,508 --> 02:44:14,002
of all German land,

1851
02:44:14,099 --> 02:44:17,839
sea and air forces in Europe...

1852
02:44:17,934 --> 02:44:21,770
to the Allied
Expeditionary Force,

1853
02:44:21,771 --> 02:44:25,895
and simultaneously
to the Soviet High Command.

1854
02:44:25,990 --> 02:44:30,211
The German war is,
therefore, at an end.

1855
02:44:30,306 --> 02:44:32,224
But let us not forget
for a moment--

1856
02:44:32,225 --> 02:44:36,348
I think it's time the guards
came into the factory.

1857
02:44:36,445 --> 02:44:39,512
Japan, with all
her treachery and greed--

1858
02:44:39,513 --> 02:44:44,788
The unconditional surrender of
Germany has just been announced.

1859
02:44:44,884 --> 02:44:48,720
At midnight tonight,
the war is over.

1860
02:44:50,735 --> 02:44:53,421
Tomorrow you'll
begin the process...

1861
02:44:53,516 --> 02:44:56,681
of looking for survivors
of your families.

1862
02:44:59,462 --> 02:45:04,066
In most cases,
you won't find them.

1863
02:45:05,217 --> 02:45:08,573
After six long years of murder,

1864
02:45:08,669 --> 02:45:13,848
victims are being mourned
throughout the world.

1865
02:45:13,944 --> 02:45:16,916
We've survived.

